                        <h4>Permutation vs. Combination</h4>
                        <p><strong>Permutation:</strong> Order matters (race places, officer positions)</p>
                        <p><strong>Combination:</strong> Order doesn't matter (committees, card hands)</p>
                        <div class="strategy"><strong>Memory Trick:</strong> "Permutation = Position matters"</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card green">
                        <h4>Bar Graph vs. Histogram</h4>
                        <p><strong>Bar Graph:</strong> GAPS between bars, categorical data</p>
                        <p><strong>Histogram:</strong> NO GAPS, numerical data</p>
                        <div class="strategy"><strong>Memory Trick:</strong> "Gaps = Groups (categories)"</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="tip-card pink">
                        <h4>Independent vs. Dependent Events</h4>
                        <p><strong>Independent:</strong> First event doesn't affect second (with replacement)</p>
                        <p><strong>Dependent:</strong> First event changes probabilities (without replacement)</p>
                        <div class="strategy"><strong>Key Question:</strong> "Does the first draw get put back?"</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
